it better since then as this was a long time ago.<br>
<br>
As for the 50 plus pets.  Pure garbage.  Thier low level wizzy spells will not outdamage the melee power of our other pets even against high mitagation mobs.  This area is suppose to be for hunting, not about pets, I know this, but if we are going to be talking about hunting then we should be talking about hunting with the best pets we can.  Honestly, earth pet, or water pet depending on your fighting style.  If you like to nuke more, water is a good choice, if you want to let your pet get beat up a bit more, then earth.  Air pet has its uses but its agility in my opinion does not make up for its lack of hp though I have used it in some cases.  The only time I have ever used the fire pets were for CoM fire guy and ixiblat fire elemental in BW.  Other than that, stay away from them.<br>
<br>
Now that im finished with that, the epic pet is a godsend, and will help mages with soloing or groups immensly so I suggest working on it as soon as you can, and if you are not in a guild able to get to the 7th island, start saving up your plat now and buy the crown.  Epic pet is completly worth using for hunting and I only wish I had it before I was level 60.<br>
<br>
By the way, chardok is very very good solo exp with the epic pet, though not quite as good with earth pet.  With epic pet and a c3 before I get to chardok I can get 1 full yellow of AA exp every hour to hour and a half.  Though I think you have to be level 60 to pull singles reliably there. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ubaxstarrsmom.showPublicProfile?language=EN>BaxstarrsMom</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#333333>(5/1/02 3:45:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=375.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: WTh is up with fire pets</span><hr size=1> Pre-50, I've found fire pets are by far the best for soloing, mostly due to the damage shield. The fastest exp comes with soloing low blues -- stuff that is blue to yellow to the pet. At 39-43 using firepet I save 70 mana per kill on not DS-ing, and the extra damage from the DS (34 per hit instead of 20) means one less nuke to get full exp, so that's another 155 mana if I'm using Blaze. So that's 225 mana per fight that I'm saving total over using an earth pet. <br>
As long as I'm not an idiot I don't get aggro from nuking. <br>
The lower hitpoints don't matter, because I kill the mobs so fast. And the mana savings are huge now that the pet regens so fact, because my mana bar is the bottleneck in downtime.<br>
<br>
Jomamer<br>
43 mage<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/useek9.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Seek 9</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 544<br> <font color=#333333>(5/3/02 6:01:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=375.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: WTh is up with fire pets</span><hr size=1> The 49, 44, 39, and 34 fire pets are very useful for <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> efficient</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> soloing.   The innate DS is the best DS in the game, pet level +1 or so.   So, if your 34th spell summons a level 28 fire pet, it's DS will be 29 -- this is better than the 49 Lava Shield.  <br>
<br>
A level 34 Mage with a Fire pet that has a 29 point DS is able to tear down blue mobs quick.<br>
<br>
The 39 pet gets enhanced regen, so even if your fire pet take 90% damage in a fight, it will regen to full in like less than a min.  The 39 fire pet is going to have a DS that is about 30+ points.<br>
<br>
If you focus your fire pets with the torch of Alna, and you chain fight low to medium blues, you can absolutely rake in the exp.<br>
<br>
Also, some people forget that DS damage is not counted to the pet's total damage output for exp allocation purposes.   So the fire pet allows the mage a much grater chance of outdamaging the pet in solo situations.<br>
<br>
Now, the original poster has Epic.   Epic is better than any Mage pet, except against mobs that have super nasty AoEs like Rak'ashir that require fire pets.  So, I don't know of any other reason why you, as an Epic-ed Mage, would want to look at using any other pet, especially level 49 fire or DDD.<br>
 <p><u>Seek Pyremaker</u><br>
Mage 54th Season, Xegony<br>
The Ring of Truth
